		<series:name><![CDATA[The Great Support Ticket System Backlog of 2013]]></series:name>
	</item>
		<item>
		<title>Support Ticket System: Code Veronica</title>
		<link>http://www.alljapaneseallthetime.com/blog/support-ticket-system-code-veronica</link>
		<comments>http://www.alljapaneseallthetime.com/blog/support-ticket-system-code-veronica#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sun, 14 Jul 2013 14:59:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[khatzumoto]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[General]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.alljapaneseallthetime.com/blog/?p=25727</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[This entry is part 2 of 2 in the series The Great Support Ticket System Backlog of 2013Resident Evil FTW! &#8220;But it&#8217;s called Biohazard in Japan, Khatz!&#8221; STFU and leave me alone! Anyway, this is a little update to let you know that a human being named Veronica is now, quite literally, taking care of&#8230;]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="seriesmeta">This entry is part 2 of 2 in the series <a href="http://www.alljapaneseallthetime.com/blog/series/the-great-support-ticket-system-backlog-of-2013" class="series-628" title="The Great Support Ticket System Backlog of 2013">The Great Support Ticket System Backlog of 2013</a></div><p>Resident Evil FTW!</p>
<p>&#8220;But it&#8217;s called Biohazard in Japan, Khatz!&#8221;</p>
<p>STFU and leave me alone! Anyway, this is a little update to let you know that a human being named Veronica is now, quite literally, taking care of business as far as <a href="http://www.alljapaneseallthetime.com/blog/contact">support ticket system issues</a> are concerned. Veronica is a real grown-up, with real children. And, well, you know what that means?</p>
<p>That&#8217;s right &#8212; she puts out the fires that my wanton, childish incompetence have created; she is order personified and she eats chaos for breakfast and then spits it out like&#8230;sugar cane <a class="simple-footnote" title="I know you. You were thinking: &#8220;here comes an eating disorder joke&#8221;. Well, no bulimia humor for you: it&#8217;s a disease, man, not a punchline&#8230;geez." id="return-note-25727-1" href="#note-25727-1"><sup>1</sup></a>. It&#8217;s like having, I dunno, adult supervision.</p>
<p>So she&#8217;s &#8212; we&#8217;ve &#8212; been at it for 2 weeks now. At this pace, another 2 weeks and everything should be back to normal backlogwise. Again, I&#8217;ll keep you posted on developments. Take care and thanks a bunch for your patience.</p>
